list.description: A black and white photo of pollen floating on the surface of water. The image is high contrast making the water black and the pollen almost totally white. There is a main branch of pollen extending from the right side of the frame and forking off light lightning to the left. In between some of the forks are swirls and bands that mimic the curvature with a larger dusted area coming in from the left. The pollen is mostly on the lower two thirds of the image with the upper third mostly the black of the water with a few ripples showing in light gray. Specs of pollen and strewn throughout the black areas like stars in the night sky.

A black and white photo looking down on a curb stop (aka parking block) at the end of a parking space. The concrete block is in the upper third of the image extending out from the left side of the image most of the way to the right side of the frame. The block is on black asphalt which takes up the top half of the frame. The lower half of the frame is white sidewalk. The side walk has a thin, vertical expansion slot close to the left side and a thicker horizontal one that's above the lower edge of the frame at the same distance the vertical one is from the left. Two dark shadows extend from the left side of the image diagonally towards the right. The top shadow begins on the right side of the top edge. The second shadow starts a third of the way down on the left side.

A black and white photo of looking down at an angle on a bench seat. The seat is made of six wood strips that are turning a corner in the frame. The strips start and end on the left side of the image with the round point of their triangle just short of the middle of the right edge of the frame. The wood in the foreground is dark. The wood at the top is almost white with the reflection of the sky above it. The background of the image is a rough sidewalk with a cross of expansion lines visible in the upper right of the image.

A black and white photo of two sections of wall that are each made up of thin, vertical strips of wood separated by dark recesses. The first wall starts on the left side of the frame and moves two thirds of the way across the frame. The curve of the way causes the gaps between the wood strips to appear thinner and thinner as it progresses. The second wall is more straight on to the camera with the space between the strips staying relatively constant. The difference in visible gaps causes the right third of the frame to be darker than the left.
A black and white photo of a set of stairs moving up and to the right. There's a dark ceiling behind the opening of the stairs which white ceiling sourround it on the lower level.

A black and white photo of the tops of concrete stairs and the edge grip treads. There are three edge grips made of strips of black material separate by thing pieces of bright metal. The lines formed by the stairs and grips cross the frame at about 45 degrees. The concrete is mostly light gray with the exception of one band that that extends from the upper left corner down to the middle of the frame at the bottom.

A black and white photo of an empty parking lot. A white line starting toward the lower right of the image moves up and across the frame to the middle of the left side. The majority of the image is taken up by the dark asphalt forming the parking spaces made by the two white lines extending perpendicular to the first line. A second set of parking space lines are at the very top of the frame with a soft focus due to being outside the primary depth of field.

A black and white photo of the ceiling of a building. The ceiling is made from dark wood planks. A balcony extends out half way in the from staring from the upper left and rounding back to the lower left to form a triangle with it's white surface. A similar triangle is formed by a white ceiling recess starting in the middle top of the image extending half way down the frame before turning back toward the upper right portion of the frame. The shape of the two white areas forms an outline of the ceiling in the shape of an arrow pointing to the lower right corner of the image.

A black and white photo of a sign painting on a will with a black field that has a white outline of a duck in flight on it with its wings extened up. There's also a small arrow pointing up in the lower left corder of the black field.

A black and white photo of three stop lights on a crossbar taken from below. The bar is at an angle across the frame moving up from the lower left to the upper right. Behind the stop lights at a lower angle are four telephone wires as well.
A black and white photo of a Sony A7c camera with a black strap attached. The camera body is black with a silver top. It rests on a wood surface. A Zeiss 35mm f/2.8 lens is mounted on the camera.

A black and white photo of the corner of a building with a white sky behind it. The image was taken at an angle that makes the corner appear like a pyramid showing two sides. The point of the pyramid is in the upper left third of the image. The side to the left crosses out of the image half way down the left site. The side on the right cuts down at an angle and leaves the frame on the bottom most of the way to the right. The walls have a texture of small, random wavy lines. A thing strip of metal flashing bands the top of the walls with a few rain drops scattered across.

A black and white photo of a painting on a wall. The central part of the image is a white fish on a black background. The background is made of birds like an M.C. Escher drawing so that the negative space in front of the fish's nose is the space between the wings and body of the bird in front of it.

A black and white photo of the white under side of a balcony with a dark color roof made of wood planks above it. The balcony starts in the upper left of the frame and moves down to the lower right. The bottom edge of the balcony is silver with a glass guard rail attached to it. The guard rail has a around metal hand rail on top. - The lower left corner of the image has black glass windows reaching up to the balcony and a glimpse of second  balcony below it.

A black and white photo of the an excavator construction vehicle on top of a mound of white sand. The main focus is the arm which is parallel to the frame of the image. It starts half way up the frame on the left side where the cab of the excavator is on the sand. The sand tapers off to the lower right side of the image where the bucket of the arm touches the ground turned slightly to where the inner side is visible. The arm is black with "DEERE" written in the middle of it in white letters. The shape of the arm frames a few palm trees in the near background.

A black and white photo of a couple walking down a beach. The horizon is roughly half way up the frame. The sky is mostly overcast with a few distinct clouds. The image is taken at an angle to the water so tide line is close to the lower left corner and extends upwards towards the horizon line on the right side.
A black and white photo of a beach. The horizon line is at the top third of the image. The sky is mostly cloudy. Waves are low with the tide's edge at the lower third of the image.
